Rwandan President Paul Kagame Sunday arrived in Tanzanian for a one-day state visit. President Kagame was received by his host President John Magufuli at the Julius Nyerere International Airport (JNIA) in Dar es Salaam. Upon disembarking the plane he was treated to traditional dance performance by cultural troupes. The two presidents then headed to the State House for talks. This is Kagameâ€™s third visit in Tanzania in the last two years. 
  
